Information about a direct payment of money from one bank account into another.

documentation.value: The name of the account that can send and receive payments to and from a payment service provider.

properties.documentation: A commercial Document issued by the Seller to the Buyer to collect payments for the goods or services provided and to state the VAT amount due by the Buyer.

documentation.value:
The date when the tax becomes accountable for the Seller and for the Buyer.
Additional Information: That date can be determined and differs from the date of issue of the invoice, according to the national implementation of the directive.

properties.documentation: Details concerning a given unit of goods, services or works mentioned in the Invoice.
Textual note that is relevant to the Invoice as a whole.

documentation.value: A textual note that gives unstructured information that is relevant to the Invoice as a whole.

properties.documentation:
A Role of an Agent that receives the payment.
Additional Information: The role of Payee may be fulfilled by another party than the Seller, e.g. a factoring service.
Information about card used for payment contemporaneous with invoice issuance.

documentation.value:
The name of the account holder of the card used for payment.
Additional Information: An account holder is the entity listed or identified as the holder of a Financial Account by the Financial Institution.
The series of digits embossed on the front of a card used for payment.
The means for how a payment is expected to be or has been settled, expressed as text.
A textual value used to establish a link between the payment and the Invoice, issued by the Seller.

properties.documentation:
A Role of an Agent that can represent an Organization for taxation purposes.
Additional Information: The Seller Tax Representative Role is not a Legal Representative.
Information about tax breakdown by different categories, rates and exemption reasons.

documentation.value: An explanation on why the amount is exempted from tax or why no tax is being charged according to the legislation, expressed as a text.

properties.documentation:
this codelist might have already been used for a different post-award module (or a subset of it). we need to investigate where it is used.
To be chosen from the entries in UNTDID 4451 [6].

The following entries from the UNTDID 4461 code list [6] may be used: - Standing instructions - SEPA Credit transfer - SEPA Direct Debit - Local Credit transfer - Non-SEPA international credit transfer - Local Direct Debit - Check - Cash - Account transfer over the books of the same payment service provider - No payment (add to balance) - Payment card

https://docs.peppol.eu/poacc/billing/3.0/codelist/UNCL2005/
The code shall distinguish between the following entries of UNTDID 2005 [6]: - Invoice date - Delivery date - Payment date

documentation.value: A unique identifier of the financial payment account, at a payment service provider, to which payment should be made.
An identifier for the payment service provider where a payment account is located.
An identifier for an object on which the invoice is based, given by the Seller.

An identifier for an object on which the invoice line is based, given by the Seller.
Additional Information: It may be a subscription number, telephone number, meter point etc., as applicable.
The means for how a payment is expected to be or has been settled, expressed as code.
An unique identifier for referencing the direct debit mandate, assigned by the Payee.
An unique banking reference identifier of the Payee or Seller, assigned by the Payee or Seller bank.
An identifier for the account to be debited by the direct debit.
An explanation on why the amount is exempted from tax or why no tax is being charged according to the legislation, expressed as a code.
